metadata.name: odium #40
metadata.description:
The idea behind "odium" is to mix the two previous works to create a new art, which maintains similarities with the previous projects, but also with its differences and peculiarities.

"odium" is based on an algorithm that I've been exploring since the "radium" and "illusions" projects. So this is the last of the series.

It is composed by with grainy/noise and flowfields, creating a glitch effect as it is finishing to render.
"odium" have random colormaps instead a configured palette system, patterns of growth and plays with randomized blendModes and colorModes, 
and I name it "odium"  because the form it grows and glitch reminds me how the hate sometimes slowly consume the mind.

This is a project made in p5.js


Omar Lobato, 04/29/2022.

metadata.name: Papercut imitation #16
metadata.description:
This art imitate the "Papercut technique" in vector illustration.
100% generative art - no additional sources used. Code only.
Features:
- 5 color palettes
- random number of layers (from 2 to 4) and random shape of layers
- random additional cut in upper layer
- rare appearance of moon
- rare appearance of crescent with a star
- very rare appearance of crescent with 2 stars
- random tree shape

metadata.name: bottle and apples #96
metadata.description:
Cycle 78 was a historic day at fxhash. When one of the biggest artists on Tezos Blockchain comes and releases his work on our beloved platform. That's right, the one and only, John Karel a.k.a jjjjjohn.

Unfortunately due to the very high price, there are many users who can't afford to buy the work. Therefore, I am here with a work that is very much inspired by jjjjjohn's work entitled "gatorade and apples" but at a very very friendly price. Same with jjjjjohn i use @PureSpider template, thank you very much.

If this piece doesn't sell out, that's okay. Maybe because my name is not jjjjjohn.
